sub_title: Member of Digital Assessment Team at Wageningen University & Research
summary:
I am an ecologist and conservationist with work experience in tourism, research, education support, non-profit organizations, and animal care. Used to working in various environments, countries and companies, I am flexible and quickly master new tasks. Sharing my knowledge and passion about wildlife is something I really enjoy, I love to see people get excited about our beautiful natural environment. I like versatility in my work and enjoy being a part of, and learning from, an (international) team, but I can also plan my own work and perform it with minimal supervision. 

Experience: 
•	NGO: Develop material for workshops, websites, reports; Background research; Funding applications: Blog writing; Development of campaign and fundraising strategies; Survey analysis
•	Research: Develop research methodology; Data collection in the field; Data management; Statistical analyses; Literature research; Report writing; Behavioural observations; Photo identification, GIS mapping
•	Tourism: Presenting information about wildlife and conservation to groups from 12 to 200 people in Dutch, German and English; Background research for presentation material; Provide customer service; Reply to queries; Administrative tasks; Blog writing
•	Animal care: Care for animals according to scientific protocols; Discuss research projects; Monitor animal welfare; Administrative tasks
•	Education support: Support university lecturers with the development and improvement of online examination material; Write and review instruction manuals; Provide live support to students
